# Claude Code per-repo settings (permissions, hooks, etc.) — local only.
.claude/

# Unreleased Codex skills staged from the future-weeks workspace.
# These live on disk for the maintainer to copy into codex/skills/ as each
# weekly bundle ships. They MUST NOT be published to the public repo until
# their release week — publishing future-week skills early is the same
# defect that prompted scripts/audit-cross-refs.sh to exist.
#
# Weekly release flow (Codex side):
#   1. Maintainer copies week-N skills from codex/future-weeks/skills/
#      into codex/skills/ (keep the future-weeks copy too).
#   2. Run `bash scripts/audit-cross-refs.sh` against claude/skills/.
#   3. Run `pwsh scripts/validate-codex-skills.ps1` against codex/skills/.
#   4. Commit the codex/skills/<new-skill>/ additions only. Never use
#      `git add -f codex/future-weeks/` — that re-introduces the leak.
#
# Mirror behaviour: the Claude side keeps its unreleased weeks in the
# sibling workspace `solo-builders-toolkit-future-weeks/skills/`, also
# outside the published repo, by the same logic.
codex/future-weeks/
